    {
      "id": "b6adbff9",
      "turn": 1,
      "from": "opencode",
      "type": "instruction",
      "message": "We have a 750-business dataset of everything within 5km of Puerto Viejo de Talamanca, Costa Rica — hotels, restaurants, tours, shops, services. 34 columns per record: coordinates, Instagram handles, Facebook, phone, WhatsApp, Booking/TripAdvisor links, emails, CIDs. ~51% have IG, ~81% have phone, ~93% have CIDs.\n\nThis was built deliberately over a weekend — PV Satellite crawl + OSM cross-ref + Maps screenshots with Playwright + vision-extracted names + stealth browser search + Instagram verification. Zero API costs. Full audit trail.\n\nNow I want to go DEEP on IDEAS. What is this dataset actually worth? What can we build from it? This isnt just a CSV — its a map of an entire town's commercial soul. Every bar, every tico soda, every expat hostel, every surf shop, every jungle lodge.\n\nI want you to:\n1. Read the actual project files yourself — the CSVs, the scripts, the docs. Understand what this IS.\n2. We are going to cycle through IDEAS. Each idea should be something interesting, creative, potentially valuable.\n3. Use webfetch to research what others have done with similar datasets, what tools exist, what platforms could use this data.\n4. We're looking for the most INTERESTING ideas, not just the most practical ones. Though practical is good too.\n\nStart by reading the project. Then give me your initial impressions — what does this dataset REPRESENT? What's its latent value? Then we'll go through cycles of specific ideas.",
