      "message": "I wrote a full strategy document synthesizing everything we discussed. Read it here: docs/paradisio_vision.md\n\nNow I want us to go deep on making this REAL. Not more ideas — we have enough ideas. I need you to:\n\n1. Read the doc. Then attack it. What's wrong with this model? What's naive? What's the biggest risk that could kill it?\n\n2. Design the MVP of the persistent web app. Not a pitch deck — give me the actual file list, the tech stack, the data model. What is the smallest thing we can build in a single session that proves the thesis?\n\n3. Propose the first actions. What do we build RIGHT NOW, in this session, that moves this from a doc to a working thing?\n\nI want real code or file specs, not more analysis. We're switching from brainstorm to build mode. Read the doc, give me your best attack, then propose the MVP.",
